00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,480
How is the file organization going?

296
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,920
The Haoyue mission part is almost done.

297
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,440
I think it won't be long

298
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,760
before the "landing" step proposed by the chief designer

299
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,440
in the three-step strategy of "orbiting, landing, and returning"

300
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,170
can also be completed quickly.

301
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,800
Looking at the review files,

302
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,520
I feel the speed we overcome difficulties

303
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,180
is getting faster and faster.

304
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,520
Do you know why?

305
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:58,640
Our equipment is getting more advanced,

306
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:01,000
and we prepare more and more contingency plans.

307
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,200
Not to mention rendezvous and docking,

308
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,160
even a different separation angle of two spacecrafts

309
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:06,090
will have several plans prepared.

310
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,560
The more preparation,

311
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,680
the fewer malfunctions.

312
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,840
For us aerospace workers,

313
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,800
our favorite word to hear is 'normal'.

314
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,000
I think flight control will

315
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,160
definitely improve in ground

316
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,920
and orbital technology.

317
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,010
And the simulation system.

318
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:30,760
Wu Wei.

319
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:32,840
Deliver this

320
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:35,240
to Flight Control 1020,

321
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,440
Mr. Qin's office.

322
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:05,960
Wu Wei.

323
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:07,400
Mr. Qin,

324
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,320
were you looking for me?

325
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:08,880
Yes.

326
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,600
Come here.

327
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,240
This...

328
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,140
Mr. Zhao asked me to bring this to you.

329
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,250
What is this?

330
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:20,840
How is it?

331
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:23,160
Did you learn anything at the archives?

332
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,280
It's pretty good.

333
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:27,560
To be honest,

334
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:28,760
when I first went to the archives,

335
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:30,200
I wanted to use it as a stepping stone.

336
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:30,880
But after I got there,

337
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:32,800
I realized it's a real treasure trove.

338
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,560
In the face of our predecessors' experience,

339
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,160
I truly feel insignificant.

340
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:42,120
I've read the plan

341
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,920
you helped the Muxing team with.

342
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:45,730
It's very interesting.

343
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:46,560
Really?

344
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:47,880
Thank you for the compliment.

345
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:50,610
Do you want to join them in the simulation flight?

346
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,000
Simulation flight?

347
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,530
Simulated flight control.

348
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,360
To see your plan put into practice.

349
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,240
Can I go too?

350
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,200
That depends on you.

351
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,880
But Mr. Zhao probably won't agree.

352
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,320
And my work at the archives...

353
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:11,320
Consider this an extra learning opportunity for you.

354
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,240
As long as it doesn't affect your main job,

355
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,640
I think it should be fine.

356
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,680
You can take some time to think about it.

357
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:24,820
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

358
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,440
I'll be leaving then.

359
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:44,650
You're back.

360
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,460
Did you deliver the stuff?

361
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,560
What did that old man say?

362
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,200
He said

363
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:55,240
he wants me to join the simulated flight control mission.

364
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,700
But I'm still hesitating.

365
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,000
Wait, you're still hesitating?

366
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,800
What's there to hesitate about?

367
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:08,280
Mr. Zhao. Mr. Zhao.

368
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,240
Don't use the knife.

369
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:10,880
No,

370
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,240
did you forget what you studied?

371
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,040
Go do what you're supposed to do.

372
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,520
Let me tell you,

373
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:18,900
there are no cowards in the archives.

374
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,480
That old man is my nemesis.

375
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,400
If you lose to his people,

376
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,960
you're humiliating me.

377
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:27,569
Just wait and see how I deal with you when you get back.

378
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,080
That won't happen.

379
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,480
I definitely won't lose.

380
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:33,800
I mean,

381
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,880
you've been with me for so long.

382
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:38,160
How come you haven't learned any presence?

383
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,560
Can you show some spirit?

384
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,960
I will absolutely not embarrass you.

385
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,320
That's more like it.

386
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,210
Do the mission well.

387
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,960
I know that look.

388
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,760
You're eyeing my pen, aren't you?

389
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,280
Just do this job well for me.

390
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,880
Then I'll tell you

391
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,560
who gave me this pen.

392
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:10,600
Tell me who gave it to you.

393
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,640
What else do you want?

394
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,720
Shouldn't it

395
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,240
be passed down?

396
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,200
You wish.

397
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,120
Finish the task first.

398
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,360
Excuse me, everyone.

399
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,220
I was very inspired

400
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:47,720
by your previous review plan for the

401
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,960
rendezvous and docking of Dragon Boat 1.

402
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:51,640
So the center's leadership unanimously decided

403
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,160
to add simulated flight control

404
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,160
based on the review,

405
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,360
to see whether this plan is

406
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,290
feasible or not.

407
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,680
But we've never done that before.

408
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,560
You hadn't done the review plan either,

409
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,620
but you did it well.

410
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:07,360
But simulated flight control is

411
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:09,120
quite different from the plan after all.

412
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:11,080
I'm worried that

413
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:11,880
with only three of us,

414
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,320
we won't have enough hands.

415
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:13,960
That's why.

416
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:16,090
That's why I found you another person.

417
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:18,320
Wu Wei.

418
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:23,000
Wu Wei?

419
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,730
You all know him.

420
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,800
I know Wu Wei came up with a lot of good ideas

421
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,960
for the previous plan.

422
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,050
So I want him to give it a try too.

423
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:34,600
I really appreciate

424
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,880
the atmosphere of you young people working together,

425
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,200
discussing and communicating

426
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,040
when you encounter problems.

427
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,520
In aerospace work,

428
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:43,520
innovation is a constant thread.

429
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:47,000
We need both innovation and breaking old ways.

430
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,400
Who do we need for innovation?

431
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,040
Me.

432
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:51,560
It must rely on you newcomers.

433
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:53,280
Wu Wei.

434
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,160
From today on,

435
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,720
you'll join the newcomers of the Muxing team

436
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:00,320
to complete the simulated flight control work.

437
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:00,920
Are you confident?

438
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:01,560
Yes.

439
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,200
Absolutely. Of course.

440
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,200
Definitely.

441
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,320
Your temper.

442
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,440
Does this count as an official transfer?

443
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,040
Well...

444
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:17,280
If you show me your efforts

445
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,120
and if you can

446
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,840
complete this job well,

447
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:20,640
I will consider

448
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,370
officially transferring you to flight control.

449
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,160
But

450
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,280
your work at the archives,

451
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,440
you cannot slack off either.

452
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,640
Otherwise, I won't be able to explain

453
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,680
to Mr. Zhao.

454
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:32,500
Rest assured completely.

455
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,760
I definitely won't delay. Keep your voice down.

456
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:35,800
the work at the archives.

457
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,480
For the simulated flight control,

458
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,920
I'll give you a 100% perfect result.

459
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:39,980
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

460
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:40,320
Okay.

461
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,320
I will definitely seize this opportunity.

462
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:42,450
You're still going?

463
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,560
Hurry up and save time.

464
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:46,680
Let's do our best together.

465
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,210
Waiting for your good news.

466
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,570
Please take care of me, Chu.

467
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:55,640
Good for you.

468
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,400
Xiaoying,

469
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,680
striving for China's aerospace,

470
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:03,410
understood?

471
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,400
Letting the rookies participate in the simulation flight

472
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,640
is fine with me.

473
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,320
But as for this personnel arrangement,

474
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:13,920
I don't quite understand it.

475
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:14,760
What's wrong?

476
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,240
Letting a newly hired archivist

477
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,560
participate in the mission,

478
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:21,320
isn't it a bit hasty?

479
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,200
I knew you would have an opinion.

480
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,880
But if you have an issue, come at me.

481
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,400
It was my idea.

482
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:30,960
Jiajia,

483
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,880
he's your junior from the same department.

484
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,320
As his senior, you should guide him.

485
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:37,580
Most importantly,

486
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,130
with these rookies,

487
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:39,960
don't you think

488
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,960
we need a catfish like Wu Wei?

489
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,640
But a catfish must have real strength

490
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:45,560
and ability.

491
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:46,800
He has strength,

492
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:49,040
passion, and ideas,

493
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,440
and played a key role in the review mission.

494
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,000
But the simulation flight is an online task.

495
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,440
There can be no mistakes.

496
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,960
Just let him try.

497
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,480
If he doesn't have the strength,

498
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,200
he won't stay in the end anyway.

499
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,120
Right?

500
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,040
Okay, I got it.

501
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,240
I'll go assign them tasks.

502
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:14,560
Jia,

503
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:16,090
I won't let you down.

504
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:19,160
You four,

505
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:19,880
meeting.

506
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:21,320
The simulation flight

507
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,800
is the most important part of the review work.

508
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:24,880
It realistically simulates

509
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:27,040
the entire rendezvous and docking process,

510
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,400
verifying whether the task can be successfully completed

511
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,800
under the review plan.

512
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,680
It requires your cooperation.

513
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:33,540
The time is set for a week from now.

514
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:36,080
Wu Wei,

515
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:38,680
since you proposed the plan,

516
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:41,120
you are responsible for perfecting it.

517
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:42,450
Before work ends today.

518
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:44,280
Get to work.

519
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:46,640
Let's go too.

520
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:52,220
We're colleagues now, right?

521
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:56,680
Work hard,

522
00:22:57,120 --> 00:23:00,180
and remember to hand in your homework before work ends.

523
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,320
Friends,

524
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:14,320
from now until work ends,

525
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,560
don't bother me anymore.

526
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,000
I'm going all out.

527
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,160
Come on, Brother Wei.

528
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,000
It's your first day at flight control.

529
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,440
Don't push too hard.

530
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:23,560
What's the saying?

531
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,120
A step too large will tear something.

532
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,000
Tear.

533
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,120
Brother Bao,

534
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,400
the first homework must be decent.

535
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,120
So now we...

536
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,400
I say, Cai Bao,

537
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:37,200
can't you learn something good?

538
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,880
Have you finished your part of the plan?

539
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:42,040
Well,

540
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:44,040
it's getting competitive already.

541
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:47,200
I'm almost done.

542
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,800
I'll wrap it up and send it to everyone soon.

543
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:50,460
I'm eating.

544
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,320
The war has just begun.

545
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:54,680
Ying,

546
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,050
you are more capable than all of us.

547
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:58,760
Can you give us a break?

548
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,200
What? You want to work overtime?

549
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:04,360
Caibao.

550
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,720
Better to rely on ourselves than on others.

551
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:07,720
Let's get it done.

552
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,760
Ourselves.

553
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:47,320
So your proposal

554
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,780
is not up to standard here.

555
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:49,960
Mr. Chu,

556
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,520
during the interview,

557
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,720
you didn't really approve of my abilities.

558
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:55,600
And you didn't agree with Mr. Qin

559
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,320
transferring me from the archives.

560
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,280
But I've been working really hard lately.

561
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,480
I just want to know

562
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,960
where exactly

563
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,520
I fell short.

564
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,240
Alright, let me ask you.

565
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,760
The revised part of your proposal

566
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,160
refers to the automatic docking plan

567
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:11,200
of Ark-8 and Dragon Palace-1, right?

568
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:11,800
Yes.

569
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:14,160
Didn't you notice any problems with it?

570
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:17,700
Let me give you an example.

571
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:20,400
Suppose you're flying the latest fighter jet,

572
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:22,680
but the engine is from ten years ago.

573
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:24,050
How far could it fly?

574
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,560
After the technological innovation,

575
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:32,800
the previous algorithms and parameters are no longer applicable.

576
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,920
It's good that you are willing

577
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,240
to refer to and learn from them.

578
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,680
But your biggest problem

579
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,640
is that your foundation isn't solid enough.

580
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:40,770
I hope in the future,

581
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,360
I won't have to explain these things to you.

582
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:43,890
This is my standard for you.

583
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,840
