870
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,840
Isn't this your plan?

871
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:12,240
Jia, Yan,

872
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,400
if you're done, hurry back.

873
00:37:14,840 --> 00:37:16,300
We'll continue tomorrow.

874
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:18,200
Someone definitely changed my parameters.

875
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:19,520
The references don't match up.

876
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,360
Let's just stick to the previous plan.

877
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:23,400
You haven't even figured out the parameters.

878
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,520
No, wait.

879
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:25,880
Even if my parameters are wrong,

880
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:26,840
it doesn't mean my plan is wrong.

881
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:27,480
I am confident.

882
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,640
This plan will definitely work,

883
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:29,840
and it better reflects our ideas.

884
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,440
Really.

885
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:33,160
Sticking to the previous plan is the safest bet.

886
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,440
We just need to perfect the subsequent steps.

887
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,120
Why?

888
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,000
When there's obviously a better choice,

889
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,040
why not take it?

890
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:38,400
Besides, this plan is very feasible.

891
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:40,200
There are many historical precedents we can refer to.

892
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:41,730
Because it's unnecessary.

893
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:45,200
Can you stop trying to be a slacker

894
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,530
and goofing off all day?

895
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:48,740
Can you put in some effort, Ying Ziqi?

896
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,320
Alright, you two.

897
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:52,880
Just talk about the ideas.

898
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:53,480
Yeah.

899
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:55,560
Nan.

900
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:57,840
I'm just focusing on the matter at hand.

901
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:58,600
I really don't believe

902
00:37:58,600 --> 00:37:59,880
that with your abilities, Ying,

903
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,320
you'd think my plan is unfeasible.

904
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:02,120
Besides, I went to the archives

905
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:03,720
and checked a lot of relevant information.

906
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,760
With our abilities, it's absolutely not a problem.

907
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,320
I didn't say your plan is unfeasible.

908
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,800
Then why not do it?

909
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,200
The purpose of the mission

910
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:11,840
is to use the safest plan

911
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:14,000
to ensure the successful completion of the simulated flight control.

912
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:15,280
Not to show off.

913
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,280
Don't impose your personal goals

914
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,680
onto the team's mission.

915
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:21,400
Just having ideas isn't enough.

916
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:24,010
What do you mean by that?

917
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,720
Choosing a better plan

918
00:38:26,240 --> 00:38:27,840
and trying hard to prove my abilities and ideas,

919
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:28,640
is that wrong?

920
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:31,880
You don't need to prove yourself.

921
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:32,800
You don't need to prove anything,

922
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,160
not because you're so strong,

923
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:36,090
but because you simply don't care.

924
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:45,960
To be honest,

925
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:47,480
I think

926
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,320
Wei's plan is quite challenging.

927
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,400
But after all, this is

928
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,800
our Muxing Team's debut.

929
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:59,240
It's better to play it safe.

930
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:02,000
Wei,

931
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:03,400
I know you've been in the archives,

932
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,880
that 'scripture library',

933
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:07,010
and you'll surely achieve greatness.

934
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:10,220
But we'll have opportunities in the future.

935
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:12,500
We don't have to rush this one, right?

936
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:16,360
Qu Ruonan,

937
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:17,480
say something.

938
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,840
I don't know what to say.

939
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:22,080
But Wu Wei,

940
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:25,380
I appreciate your attitude and determination.

941
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:26,960
As for the proposal,

942
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:30,120
I lean more towards Ying Ziqi's.

943
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:32,960
Although compared to yours,

944
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:34,840
it's a bit too conservative.

945
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:36,320
But his proposal

946
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:39,240
is safer and more reliable,

947
00:39:39,240 --> 00:39:40,720
and backed by more data.

948
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:44,680
Yes.

949
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:46,440
I admit with my current abilities,

950
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,160
it's hard to convince you all.

951
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:51,280
But I really think we should try.

952
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:52,440
It's just a simulation.

953
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,720
Why can't we test it?

954
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:54,980
What are you afraid of?

955
00:39:57,360 --> 00:39:58,400
We aren't afraid,

956
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:00,540
and we don't distrust you.

957
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,000
We just want to

958
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,080
complete the task,

959
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:05,360
that's all.

960
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:07,500
But you weren't like this before.

961
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:09,880
Where's that drive you had as a kid?

962
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:10,680
Ying Ziqi.

963
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:12,320
I might not be as capable as you,

964
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,050
but at least I'm willing to try.

965
00:40:14,640 --> 00:40:16,160
You were specially recruited.

966
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:16,680
You took a spot

967
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:18,400
that so many dream of.

968
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,600
What are you here for?

969
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:20,720
You clock out on time

970
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:21,640
and play games in the dorm.

971
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:22,800
What have you achieved?

972
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,130
We're a team, aren't we?

973
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:25,040
Right?

974
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:29,120
Now I seriously doubt your attitude.

975
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:30,480
You don't cherish this at all.

976
00:40:30,480 --> 00:40:31,800
That's none of your business.

977
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:32,760
Of course it is.

978
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:34,720
Enough.

979
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,560
Stop arguing.

980
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,560
Just because it's called a dorm,

981
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:40,890
do you still think you're high schoolers?

982
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:43,680
I don't care about your past grudges.

983
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,000
That has nothing to do

984
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:46,730
with today's proposal choice.

985
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,640
Since everyone has ideas,

986
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,120
let's go with whoever has

987
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:52,040
the highest overall score.

988
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:52,840
Okay?

989
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,680
The specific proposal

990
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,480
will be decided the day after tomorrow.

991
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,120
Nan.

992
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:58,680
Nan.

993
00:40:59,520 --> 00:41:00,120
Nan.

994
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:28,960
Aerospace Flight Control.

995
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:38,960
Sorry to bother you, Mr. Chu.

996
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:40,360
I want to ask you

997
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:42,220
about my proposal's parameters.

998
00:41:45,520 --> 00:41:47,360
The parameters are inconsistent.

999
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:48,490
Did you change them?

1000
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:50,800
What do you mean, Wu Wei?

1001
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:52,360
Mr. Chu helped you so much.

1002
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:54,280
Are you misunderstanding something?

1003
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,410
If you changed them,

1004
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:56,960
why didn't you tell me?

1005
00:41:58,480 --> 00:41:59,800
Yes, I changed them.

1006
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:02,300
Because you cited the wrong parameters.

1007
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:04,080
The reason I didn't tell you

1008
00:42:04,080 --> 00:42:06,360
was hoping you'd check the rest yourself.

1009
00:42:06,360 --> 00:42:07,960
Is there a problem with that?

1010
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,080
Don't you check

1011
00:42:10,080 --> 00:42:11,280
your own plans?

1012
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:13,810
My parameters just weren't accurate enough.

1013
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:16,080
You could have told me if you thought they were wrong.

1014
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:17,120
And how did you know

1015
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:18,400
that was my final plan?

1016
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,860
Just not accurate enough?

1017
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:22,880
Wu Wei, you work in aerospace.

1018
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:24,600
In our industry,

1019
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,080
there is no room for error,

1020
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,160
otherwise it leads to catastrophic disasters.

1021
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:31,690
And you have the nerve to tell me it just wasn't accurate enough?

1022
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:41,400
Forget it. It's nothing.

1023
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:42,360
Go back to work.
